&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Pharmacy Technical Assistant - Operational Services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 - Part Time (11.4 hours per week) - Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have an exciting opportunity within the Pharmacy department for an enthusiastic and motivated assistant to join our busy team on a part time basis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is a rotational position and will involve working within the Main Dispensary and Pharmacy Stores:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within the&lt;strong&gt; Inpatient Dispensary&lt;/strong&gt; you will dispense inpatient prescriptions, prepare out-of-hours kits and cover our reception hatch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within &lt;strong&gt;Stores and Distribution&lt;/strong&gt; you will receive goods from suppliers and load our state-of-the-art robot. You will also be responsible for the supply of stock items to wards and departments within our hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be offered a variety of experience and training within each area of your rotation, and will, as part of our Apprenticeship Programme, work towards achieving an NVQ Level 2 in Pharmacy Services (if not already achieved). Ideally you should have GCSE Mathematics and English, grade C or above for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have an eye for detail, excellent communication skills and desire to work within a friendly team this job is for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you would like to talk to somebody about this vacancy then please contact:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rowena Moore, Lead Technician Dispensary Services Ph: 01483 571122 Ext 4013&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Melina Healey, Lead Technician Stores &amp; Distribution Ph: 01483 571122 Ext 2134&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
